cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD

This paper involves the development of a new method for synapse detection using fluorescence microscopy and image analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of probabilistic models, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of unsupervised learning, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of large datasets, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SD (Software Engineering).
